Members of Congress from the Republican Party have expressed their support for President Trump's nomination of Mike Pompeo as the next Secretary of State. Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell, Speaker of the House Paul Ryan, and other senators and representatives have praised Pompeo's leadership skills, experience, and dedication to national security. They believe that Pompeo's background as CIA Director and his relationships with world leaders make him an excellent choice for the role. Cabinet members, including Ambassador to the United Nations Nikki Haley and Director of the Office of Management and Budget Mick Mulvaney, have also congratulated Pompeo on his nomination.